hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Scale factor and initial value:
$$a(t)=C\,t^{2/3},\qquad a_i=a(t_i)=C\,t_i^{2/3}\,. $$

2. Peculiar momentum redshifts as $p_{\rm phys}\propto a^{-1}$, so for nonrelativistic particle
$$m\,v_p(t)\propto a^{-1}(t)\quad\Longrightarrow\quad v_p(t)=v_0\,\frac{a_i}{a(t)}\,. $$

3. Comoving coordinate velocity:
$$v_p(t)=a(t)\,\frac{dr}{dt}\quad\Longrightarrow\quad \frac{dr}{dt}=\frac{v_p(t)}{a(t)}
=\frac{v_0\,a_i}{a^2(t)}\,. $$

4. Substitute $a(t)=C\,t^{2/3}$ and $a_i=C\,t_i^{2/3}$:
$$\frac{dr}{dt}
=\frac{v_0\,C\,t_i^{2/3}}{C^2\,t^{4/3}}
=\frac{v_0\,t_i^{2/3}}{C\,t^{4/3}}\,. $$

5. Integrate from $t_i$ to $\infty$ to get $r_{\max}$:
$$r_{\max}
=\int_{t_i}^{\infty}\frac{v_0\,t_i^{2/3}}{C\,t^{4/3}}\,dt
=\frac{v_0\,t_i^{2/3}}{C}\int_{t_i}^{\infty}t^{-4/3}dt
=\frac{v_0\,t_i^{2/3}}{C}\Bigl[-3\,t^{-1/3}\Bigr]_{t_i}^{\infty}
=\frac{3\,v_0\,t_i^{2/3}\,t_i^{-1/3}}{C}
=\frac{3\,v_0\,t_i^{1/3}}{C}\,. $$

6. Eliminate $C$ via $C=a_i/t_i^{2/3}$:
$$r_{\max}
=\frac{3\,v_0\,t_i^{1/3}}{(a_i/t_i^{2/3})}
=\frac{3\,v_0\,t_i}{a_i}\,. $$
